title: For Sale:  Titanium Nitride Gold Gun Part Coating
postcontent:
Greetings,
I can coat any steel, stainless steel part for you with Titanium Nirtride GOLD: Please email me with any questions: REDACTED
**********************************************************************
Titanium Nitride 
TiN is an extremely hard ceramic material, often used as a coating on titanium alloys, tool steel, stainless steel, carbon steel and other metallic components to improve the substrate's surface properties.  Common applications include aerospace parts, military components, medical implants, cutting tools, industrial parts, manufacturing dies / molds and dental and orthodontic appliances.  TiN is a beautiful gold color and is often used as a wear resistant alternative to elemental gold plating. 

Applied as a thin coating, TiN is used to provide a hard surface to protect cutting and sliding surfaces and for decorative purposes (due to its gold appearance).  It is also used as a non-toxic barrier on the exterior of medical implants and jewelry.  TiN has a low coefficient of friction and an operating temperature of more than 1,000 degrees Fahrenheit. title: For Sale:  Titanium Nitride Gold Coating of Gun Parts
postcontent:
Greetings,
I can coat any steel, stainless steel part for you with Titanium Nirtride GOLD: Please email me with any questions: pmic98039@gmail.com
**********************************************************************
Titanium Nitride 
TiN is an extremely hard ceramic material, often used as a coating on titanium alloys, tool steel, stainless steel, carbon steel and other metallic components to improve the substrate's surface properties.  Common applications include aerospace parts, military components, medical implants, cutting tools, industrial parts, manufacturing dies / molds and dental and orthodontic appliances.  TiN is a beautiful gold color and is often used as a wear resistant alternative to elemental gold plating. 

Applied as a thin coating, TiN is used to provide a hard surface to protect cutting and sliding surfaces and for decorative purposes (due to its gold appearance).  It is also used as a non-toxic barrier on the exterior of medical implants and jewelry.  TiN has a low coefficient of friction and an operating temperature of more than 1,000 degrees Fahrenheit.  In most applications a coating of less than 5 micrometers (0.00020 in) is applied.  

We apply TiN using a technique called cathodic arc PVD, or physical vapor deposition.  This method is environmentally friendly and produces a functional coating unlike some other methods which are strictly decorative in nature.  Our coatings comply with aerospace specification AMS 2444A.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Upgraded M&M M10 AK-47
postcontent:
Looking to make some room in my safe so yet another AK is up on the chopping block.

Real nice and straight M10 AK that has had some upgrades done to it, the big upgrades are geared towards reliability, longevity, shootability and some minor aesthetics upgrades as well 

Stuff I added;
Thinner front sight post, makes distance shooting a bit easier
Modified to fit norinco Mak-90 gas piston tube, these have 8 gas ports to dissipate gas pressure during cycling. Results in softer recoil, longer action life (no more carrier bashing into the rear trunnion) and actually help the action stay a bit cleaner and cooler. 
Replaced the fixed stock with a polish tantal sidefolder, benefits speak for themselves on this one, trashed the tapco POS polymer stock.
Replaced the recoil spring with a Wolff extra power, again that's fairly self explanatory. 
Damage industries ported muzzle brake, more effective than the AK-74 muzzle brake in recoil reduction and substantially better in its flash hiding capabilities. 
Surplus bulgarian canvas sling in OD - best slings out there for the AK, simple and robust. 
Custom made AK light mount, mounts between barrel and gas tube, 2in metal picatinny rail section, sorry the TLR-4 in the picture doesn't come with unless you want to add some cash
Egyptian Maadi wood handguards, these are kinda rare and a personal favorites of mine due to palm swell and they're just awesome looking to boot. Still have the quadrail it came with, comes with it. 

Stuff that the M10 features out of the box;
Factory RPK sight that makes sighting in an AK a real painless process instead of dicking around with the front sight tool. 
Factory side mount scope rail for optics
Factory hogue pistol grip, much more comfortable than the commie grips that seem to be made for underfed children

Besides that, great running and looking AK that is straight and lighter than most comparable AK's featuring all new parts and a much better build quality than WASR-10's. Not too mention this AK rivals my Norinco type 56 in accuracy which isn't fair 'cause the norinco was a good bit more expensive. The recoil spring and damage industries muzzle brake really cuts down on recoil too.  Last but not least the magwell is CNC cut on these and mag fitment is excellent with every mag I own, tight lockup and negligible wobble. I will throw in a couple mags. 

Fastest way to reach me would be via text, or give me a ring at 314-941-60three3

postcontent:
On gunbroker.com - type in "432004322" into the search line...
This is an AMAZING work of art! This rifle was hand crafted back in 64 according to date on barrel and Gunsmiths personal signature stamped on barrel ahead of forearm. It's been my pride and joy to own as a functional piece of art of bygone days of such outstanding craftsmanship. I've shot a box of 1990's Winchester factory silver box ammo and it was sub-MOA all day long ;-). RARE to find such a period correct 264 Mag with a barrel in such outstanding condition (i.e. not shot-out). To produce this quality today would be astronomical in cost, and with the beautiful arsenic produced bluing - virtually impossible to reproduce. Incredible lines on the custom carved laminated stock with what appears to be Rosewood caps with diamond inlays (Bone?). Nice patina to the hand-rubbed finish to provide that golden coloration to the maple laminates. includes a Leupold AO 10x scope and Leupold mounts. Beautiful deep arsenic old process blue that give it the rich deep true blue not black) bluing color. Good luck on finding another one this fine...one slight scratch on the grip cap below the diamond and some touchup to the annodized floorplate...otherwise pristine!

postcontent:
https://www.extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=277

For those needing/wanting a Lead-Free, HEAVY 357 Magnum load, generating full power plus, here it is.

Below are real world velocities taken from my personal real world stock guns. The established use of long laboratory test barrels that give false high velocity readings is essentially misleading to the public who won’t be firing ammo from a laboratory test barrel in the real world, where it matters.

2145 fps - Marlin mod 1894, 18 inch barrel
1583 fps - S&W mod 27, 5 inch barrel
1591 fps - S&W Mt. Gun, 4 inch barrel
1507 fps - S&W mod 66, 3 inch barrel
1448 fps - S&W mod 66, 2.5 inch barrel
You’ll notice that the newer S&W 4 inch Mt Gun gave higher velocities than the older 5 inch model 27 S&W and this is because of different internal barrel dynamics of the newer gun.

Due to the long-for-weight all copper bullet, we did not have the case capacity to use a bulky flash retarded powder and thus there is noticeable muzzle flash with this load, except when firing it from the rifle, which yielded little to no flash.

This load is the typical Barn-Burning, Turbo-Charged, Buffalo Bore type of HEAVY 357 mag. load and as such, should only be used in revolvers made of all steel. It should not be fired in light weight alloy framed or cylindered revolvers. Feel free to use it in ALL/ANY 357 mag. chambered rifles and all steel revolvers.
